cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper discusses decision-theoretic agents and their ability to predict and evaluate the results of their actions using a model or ontology of their environment. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the agents' goals and utility functions, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the need for a well-defined procedure for resolving ontological crises, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
